The paper discusses privacy concerns related to sharing data, which is a common issue in the field of database systems (cs.DB). The proposed method uses generative adversarial networks (GANs), which is a popular technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the limitations of traditional anonymization and perturbation techniques, which are commonly used in the field of computer security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed method using real-world datasets, which is a common practice in the field of social and information sciences (cs.SI).
